<p><strong>How to fix:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Open your Excel file.</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make sure the <strong>first row</strong> (the headers) are exactly:</p>
<ul>
<li><code node="[object Object]">CONCENTRATION</code></li>
<li><code node="[object Object]">VIABILITY %</code></li>
</ul>
<p>For example, the first two columns should look like:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th>CONCENTRATION</th><th>VIABILITY %</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>10</td><td>95</td></tr><tr><td>50</td><td>87</td></tr><tr><td>...</td><td>...</td></tr></tbody></table>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>No extra spaces</strong> before or after the column names.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>No different spellings</strong>, e.g. not <code node="[object Object]">Concentration</code>, <code node="[object Object]">concentration</code>, <code node="[object Object]">Viability %</code>, or <code node="[object Object]">VIABILITY%</code>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Tips:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>If you’re using a non-English version of Excel, make sure the column names are in English as above.</li>
<li>If you copy/pasted data, sometimes hidden spaces are added—double-click the header cell and check.</li>
<li>Save the file and try again.</li>
