A row labeled "Mean Viability Extract 1".

A row labeled "Mean Viability Extract 2".

Raw triplicates for each extract (yellow = Extract 1, orange = Extract 2).

2. Analysis Rules

IC50 Calculation

Use only the rows:

"Mean Viability Extract 1"

"Mean Viability Extract 2"

Fit a 4-parameter log-logistic model (LL.4) using the drc package.

Extract the IC50 for each extract separately.

Standard Deviation

For Extract 1: calculate the overall standard deviation from its raw triplicates (yellow cells).

For Extract 2: calculate the overall standard deviation from its raw triplicates (orange cells).

Note: Standard deviation is per extract, not per concentration (so only one SD per extract).

Dose–Response Curves

Plot curves for each extract:

X-axis = Concentration (log scale).

Y-axis = Mean viability (%).

Show experimental points + fitted curve.

Add a dashed vertical line at IC50.

Title format:

"Analysed Plate Extract 1"

"Analysed Plate Extract 2"

3. Output

Generate one Excel file with the following sheets:

"Analysed Plate Extract 1"

Concentrations

Mean viability values (from input row)

IC50 value

Standard deviation (single number for the extract)

Predicted curve data

