<hr>
<h2><strong>Automated R Script Plan</strong></h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Input</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>The script will read the Excel file and <strong>auto-detect</strong> the rows:
<ul>
<li>"Concentration"</li>
<li>"Mean Viability Extract 1"</li>
<li>"Mean Viability Extract 2"</li>
<li>Raw triplicates for each extract (yellow = Extract 1, orange = Extract 2)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Analysis</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>IC50</strong>: Fit a 4-parameter log-logistic model (LL.4) for each extract’s mean row vs. concentration.</li>
<li><strong>Standard Deviation</strong>: Compute <strong>one SD per extract</strong> from all its triplicate values (yellow or orange).</li>
<li><strong>Plotting</strong>: Generate a dose–response plot for each extract with:
<ul>
<li>Experimental points</li>
<li>Fitted curve</li>
<li>Vertical dashed line at IC50</li>
<li>Title as required</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Output Excel</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>One file, two sheets ("Analysed Plate Extract 1", "Analysed Plate Extract 2"), each including:
<ul>
<li>Concentrations</li>
<li>Mean viability (from input)</li>
<li>IC50 value</li>
<li>Standard deviation (one value)</li>
<li>Predicted curve data</li>
<li><em>Plots will be saved as PNGs; Excel embedding is not native to base R but can be done with <code node="[object Object]">openxlsx</code> if desired.</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Do you want images embedded in Excel or as separate PNG files?</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Embedding in Excel is possible via the <code node="[object Object]">openxlsx</code> package, but not via <code node="[object Object]">writexl</code>.</li>
<li>PNGs in the same folder is simpler and works everywhere.</li>
<li><strong>Default will be: Excel with all data, plus PNG files.</strong><br>
<em>(Let me know if you want embedded images and I’ll adapt the script.)</em></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Ready-to-use Script</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Below is a script that:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Reads your data sheet (as shown)</li>
<li>Auto-detects and processes the required rows</li>
<li>Outputs Excel sheets and PNGs as requested</li>
</ul>
