<hr>
<h3>1. <strong>Why doesn’t the curve connect each experimental point with a line?</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>What you see:</strong><br>
In your plot, the fitted (predicted) dose–response line is <strong>not</strong> simply connecting each experimental point. Instead, it is a smooth curve, and your experimental points are shown as individual dots.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Why:</strong><br>
The fitted curve is <strong>not</strong> a “connect-the-dots” line.<br>
It’s the best-fit solution to the 4-parameter log-logistic model (<code node="[object Object]">LL.4</code>), which mathematically describes the overall trend of how viability responds to dose.</p>
<ul>
<li>The predicted values are calculated for a <strong>smooth range of concentrations</strong> (usually many more values than in your raw data) to show the continuous model fit.</li>
<li>The <strong>experimental points</strong> are your actual measurements; the curve is the model’s estimate.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>If you want a line connecting only your experimental points:</strong><br>
Add <code node="[object Object]">geom_line()</code> with your data (not the predicted curve):</p>
<figure class="CodeBlock-module__container--QRI4L CodeBlock-module__immersive--D8NjT" aria-labelledby=":r9t:"><div class="CodeBlock-module__header--K8Zrp"><span class="LanguageDot-module__languageDot--O6n2z" style="background-color: rgb(25, 140, 231);"></span><span id=":r9t:" class="CodeBlock-module__languageName--fxI6n">R</span><button data-component="IconButton" type="button" class="prc-Button-ButtonBase-c50BI prc-Button-IconButton-szpyj" data-loading="false" data-no-visuals="true" data-size="medium" data-variant="invisible" aria-describedby=":r9v:-loading-announcement" aria-labelledby=":r9u:"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M1 13h3M1 3h14"></path><path fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1 7.25a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h11.5a1.75 1.75 0 1 1 0 3.5H9.536v-.464a.679.679 0 0 0-1.086-.543l-1.619 1.214a.68.68 0 0 0 0 1.086l1.619 1.214a.679.679 0 0 0 1.086-.543v-.464H12.5a3.25 3.25 0 0 0 0-6.5z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></button><span class="prc-TooltipV2-Tooltip-cYMVY" data-direction="s" aria-hidden="true" id=":r9u:" popover="auto">Wrap</span></div><div class="CodeBlock-module__copyContainer--jLoHL"><div class="CodeBlock-module__copyContent--BH7EX"><button data-component="IconButton" type="button" class="prc-Button-ButtonBase-c50BI CodeBlock-module__copyButton--eyFr8 prc-Button-IconButton-szpyj" data-loading="false" data-no-visuals="true" data-size="medium" data-variant="invisible" aria-describedby=":ra2:-loading-announcement" aria-labelledby=":ra0:"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" class="octicon octicon-copy" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" display="inline-block" overflow="visible" style="vertical-align: text-bottom;"><path d="M0 6.75C0 5.784.784 5 1.75 5h1.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-1.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 