<h2>2. <strong>Predicted Viabilities Not in Percent</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>If your input is in percent, the predicted values from the model (<code node="[object Object]">predict()</code>) <strong>will also be in percent</strong>.</li>
<li>If you see values not in percent (e.g., 0.8 instead of 80), it means there is a conversion error in the code—possibly a division by 100 or a column that was inadvertently scaled.</li>
<li><strong>Check that you NEVER divide by 100 or multiply by 100 in your script</strong> if your input is already in percent.</li>
</ul>
