	C14.4974,19.3114,14.4848,20.1128,14.4848,20.4914z"></path></svg></div></div></div></div><div class="ChatMessage-module__content--sWQll"><div class="js-snippet-clipboard-copy-unpositioned ChatMessage-module__messageArea--gxJTG"><h3 class="sr-only">Copilot said: If your Excel input values are already</h3><div class="markdown-body MarkdownRenderer-module__container--dNKcF MarkdownViewer-module__markdownOverrides--xtpOl" data-copilot-markdown="true" style="--MarkdownRenderer_streaming-fade-duration: 750ms;"><p>If your Excel input values are already in <strong>percentage</strong> (for example, 93.01, 115.83, etc.), but the script is still plotting or outputting <strong>decimals</strong> (like 0.9301, 1.1583), then somewhere in the script your values are being converted to decimals—often accidentally by a division by 100.</p>
<h3><strong>Why This Happens:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Common cause:</strong> The <code node="[object Object]">drm()</code> function or parts of your R script may expect values between 0 and 100 (percent), but if code somewhere divides by 100 (like <code node="[object Object]">mean1/100</code>), it will convert percent to decimal.</li>
<li><strong>Reading from Excel:</strong> Sometimes, Excel stores percentages as decimals (e.g., 0.93 with a percent format), but when displayed in Excel, you see 93%. R will read it as 0.93 unless the cell is formatted as "General" or "Number".</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2><strong>How to Diagnose and Fix</strong></h2>
<h3>1. <strong>Print the Values Immediately After Reading</strong></h3>
<p>Add this just after reading from Excel:</p>
<figure class="CodeBlock-module__container--QRI4L CodeBlock-module__immersive--D8NjT" aria-labelledby=":rc2:"><div class="CodeBlock-module__header--K8Zrp"><span class="LanguageDot-module__languageDot--O6n2z" style="background-color: rgb(25, 140, 231);"></span><span id=":rc2:" class="CodeBlock-module__languageName--fxI6n">R</span><button data-component="IconButton" type="button" class="prc-Button-ButtonBase-c50BI prc-Button-IconButton-szpyj" data-loading="false" data-no-visuals="true" data-size="medium" data-variant="invisible" aria-describedby=":rc4:-loading-announcement" aria-labelledby=":rc3:"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M1 13h3M1 3h14"></path><path fill="currentColor" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M1 7.25a.75.75 0 0 0 0 1.5h11.5a1.75 1.75 0 1 1 0 3.5H9.536v-.464a.679.679 0 0 0-1.086-.543l-1.619 1.214a.68.68 0 0 0 0 1.086l1.619 1.214a.679.679 0 0 0 1.086-.543v-.464H12.5a3.25 3.25 0 0 0 0-6.5z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></button><span class="prc-TooltipV2-Tooltip-cYMVY" data-direction="s" aria-hidden="true" id=":rc3:" popover="auto">Wrap</span></div><div class="CodeBlock-module__copyContainer--jLoHL"><div class="CodeBlock-module__copyContent--BH7EX"><button data-component="IconButton" type="button" class="prc-Button-ButtonBase-c50BI CodeBlock-module__copyButton--eyFr8 prc-Button-IconButton-szpyj" data-loading="false" data-no-visuals="true" data-size="medium" data-variant="invisible" aria-describedby=":rc7:-loading-announcement" aria-labelledby=":rc5:"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" class="octicon octicon-copy" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" display="inline-block" overflow="visible" style="vertical-align: text-bottom;"><path d="M0 6.75C0 5.784.784 5 1.75 5h1.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-1.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 .25-.25v-1.5a.75.75 0 0 1 1.5 0v1.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 9.25 16h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 0 14.25Z"></path><path d="M5 1.75C5 .784 5.784 0 6.75 0h7.5C15.216 0 16 .784 16 1.75v7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 14.25 11h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0 1 5 9.25Zm1.75-.25a.25.25 0 0 0-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 0 0 .25-.25v-7.5a.25.25 0 0 0-.25-.25Z"></path></svg></button><span class="CopyToClipboardButton-module__tooltip--HDUYz prc-TooltipV2-Tooltip-cYMVY" data-direction="s" aria-label="Copy code" aria-hidden="true" id=":rc5:" popover="auto">Copy code</span></div></div><div class="CodeBlock-module__codeContainer--snQei"><pre class="CodeBlock-module__code--gyjSL" tabindex="0"><code class="">print<span class="hljs-punctuation" node="[object Object]">(</span>mean1<span class="hljs-punctuation" node="[object Object]">)</span>
print<span class="hljs-punctuation" node="[object Object]">(</span>mean2<span class="hljs-punctuation" node="[object Object]">)</span>
</code></pre></div></figure>
<ul>
<li>If you see values like <code node="[object Object]">93.01, 115.83</code> → already percent, no conversion needed.</li>
<li>If you see <code node="[object Object]">0.9301, 1.1583</code> → they are decimals and need to be multiplied by 100.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
