<hr>
<h2>1. <strong>Flag Outliers (Points Far from the Fitted Curve)</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>After fitting the curve, compute the <strong>residual</strong> for each experimental point:
<ul>
<li>Residual = |Observed viability − Predicted viability|</li>
<li>Flag as an outlier if the residual is above a certain threshold (e.g., &gt;2× standard deviation of residuals, or user-defined).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Mark outliers on the plot and in the Excel output.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>2. <strong>Let the User Choose Output Folder</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Instead of saving to the working directory, prompt the user to select a folder (using <code node="[object Object]">tk_choose.dir()</code>).</li>
<li>All output files (Excel, PNGs) will be saved there.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>3. <strong>Interactive Shiny App</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>The above features can be included in a Shiny app, allowing:
<ul>
<li>File/folder selection.</li>
<li>Drag-and-drop file upload.</li>
<li>Outlier threshold adjustment.</li>
<li>Immediate plot display.</li>
<li>Download results.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
