<hr>
<h3><strong>D. For Shiny Apps</strong></h3>
<p>A Shiny app will always offer a file/folder upload interface in your browser, even if <code node="[object Object]">tcltk</code> does not work.</p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Summary Table</strong></h2>
<table><thead><tr><th>Environment</th><th style="text-align: center;">Pop-ups work?</th><th>Suggestions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>RStudio Desktop</td><td style="text-align: center;">✔️</td><td>Should work</td></tr><tr><td>RGui (Windows)</td><td style="text-align: center;">✔️</td><td>Should work</td></tr><tr><td>RStudio Server/web</td><td style="text-align: center;">❌</td><td>Use manual paths or Shiny</td></tr><tr><td>Terminal/SSH</td><td style="text-align: center;">❌</td><td>Use manual paths or Shiny</td></tr><tr><td>Mac/Linux Desktop</td><td style="text-align: center;">✔️</td><td>May need XQuartz/tcltk</td></tr></tbody></table>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Let Me Know:</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Are you running R in a GUI (RStudio Desktop or RGui) or in a terminal/server?</li>
<li>Do you want a version where you paste the file/output paths directly?</li>
<li>Or would you like a Shiny app template for full interactive GUI?</li>
</ul>
