<ul>
<li><strong>Drag-and-drop multiple Excel files</strong> (or select using file picker)</li>
<li><strong>Output folder selection</strong></li>
<li><strong>Interactive outlier threshold adjustment</strong> (slider)</li>
<li><strong>Immediate plot display for both extracts per file</strong></li>
<li><strong>Flag outliers (points far from fitted curve) in red</strong></li>
<li><strong>Download Excel results with embedded plots and PNGs for each file</strong></li>
<li><strong>Percent auto-detection</strong> (as in your batch script)</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Shiny App Structure</h2>
<p>Below is a single-file Shiny app. Save it as <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code> and run it with <code node="[object Object]">shiny::runApp("app.R")</code> or click "Run App" in RStudio.</p>
