</code></pre></div></figure>
(replace <code node="[object Object]">"path/to/your/app_folder"</code> with the folder where <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code> is saved.)</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2><strong>6. Reusing the App Later</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>Every time you want to use your app, just:
<ul>
<li>Open RStudio.</li>
<li>Open your <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code> file.</li>
<li>Click <strong>"Run App"</strong>.</li>
<li>Or use the <code node="[object Object]">shiny::runApp()</code> command as above.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2><strong>7. (Optional) Add to GitHub</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>You can add your <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code> file to your GitHub repo (e.g., <a href="https://github.com/mwauradominic935-cell/Cytocity-Analysis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cytocity-Analysis</a>) for safekeeping and easy sharing.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><strong>Summary Table</strong></h3>
<table><thead><tr><th>Task</th><th>How-To</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Save script</td><td>File &gt; Save As &gt; Choose <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code></td></tr><tr><td>Run in RStudio</td><td>Open <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code>, click "Run App"</td></tr><tr><td>Run from console</td><td><code node="[object Object]">shiny::runApp("path/to/app_folder")</code></td></tr><tr><td>Reuse</td><td>Just repeat above steps—no retyping needed!</td></tr><tr><td>Backup/share</td><td>Add <code node="[object Object]">app.R</code> to your GitHub repo</td></tr></tbody></table>
